        Parameters:
        mutationList - the mutation list to compare against
        comparator - the comparator used to determine whether or not mutations are equal

    • Method Detail

      • getResult

        public java.lang.Object getResult()
        After this Adapter has been applied to an AsiGrammar tree (i.e. meaning the grammar tree has been evaluated according to the logic of this class). You may invoke this function to retrieve the score obtained. If the statement was constructed to return a boolean value, then this function will return TRUE_VALUE for true and FALSE_VALUE for false. If the statement was constructed to return a score, the exact numerical score will be returned.
        Specified by:
        getResult in interface AsiGrammarEvaluator
        Returns:
        the score the AsiGrammar tree evaluated to
        See Also:
        AsiGrammarEvaluator.getResult()

      • caseAResidueResidue

        public void caseAResidueResidue(AResidueResidue node)
        The residue production is used for evaluating whether or not the specified residue is IN the mutation list. Given the two properties of the residue node, amino acid list and codon number, create a mutation and compare it to each element in the list. If the mutation IS found, push TRUE onto the stack, otherwise push FALSE.
        Specified by:
        caseAResidueResidue in interface Analysis
        Overrides:
        caseAResidueResidue in class DepthFirstAdapter
        Parameters:
        node - the residue node to be evaluated

      • caseAResiduenotResidue

        public void caseAResiduenotResidue(AResiduenotResidue node)
        The residue not production is used for evaluating whether or not the specified NOT residue is IN the mutation list. Given the two properties of the residue node, amino acid list and codon number, create a mutation and compare it to each element in the list. If the mutation is NOT found, push TRUE onto the stack, otherwise push FALSE.

      • caseAResidueinvertResidue

        public void caseAResidueinvertResidue(AResidueinvertResidue node)
        The residue not production is used for evaluating whether or not the specified NOT residue is IN the mutation list. Given the two properties of the residue node, amino acid list and codon number, create a mutation, invert it and compare it to each element in the list. If the mutation is found, push TRUE onto the stack, otherwise push FALSE.
        Specified by:
        caseAResidueinvertResidue in interface Analysis

        See Also:
        e.g. 41(NOT L)

      • caseASelectlist

        public void caseASelectlist(ASelectlist node)
        The select list production is used to count how many items in the list evaluated to TRUE. The function will iterate though this list, removing each individual residue's truth value, and push on a total count of residues that evaluated to TRUE.
